\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 35. S. porophylla} Bertol. in Desv.,{\i Jour. Bot. Appl.}{\b  4}: 76 (1814) ({\i S. media} auct. ital. non Gouan). Rosettes fairly flat. Leaves 4-15 × 2-3 mm, oblanceolate, mucronate, with 5-11 hydathodes. Flowering stem 3-8 cm, with 4-7(-12) flowers. Calyx and hypanthium dull, rather pale pink, sometimes tinged with green, rarely red.{\i  Limestone rocks and screes above} 1000{\i  m. C. & S. Italy.} It.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 36. S. federici-augusti} Biasol., {\i Relaz. Viaggio} 109 (1841) ({\i S. frederici-augusti} auct., {\i S. media} subsp. {\i porophylla} sensu Hayek, pro parte; incl.{\i  S. porophylla} var. {\i montenegrina} (Halácsy & Bald.) Engler & Irmscher). Rosettes regular, flat. Leaves 12-35 × 3-8 mm, oblanceolate to spathulate, usually mucronate. Flowering stem 7-20 cm, with 10-20 flowers. Inflorescence bright or dark red.{\i  Limestone rocks. Balkan peninsula, from central Crna Gora to E.C. Greece.} Al Gr Ju.
\par

