\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 37. S. sempervivum} C. Koch,{\i  Linnaea }{\b 19}: 40 (1846) ({\i S.porophylla} var.{\i  sibthorpiana} (Griseb.) Engler & Irmscher; incl.{\i  S. media }subsp. {\i porophylla} sensu Hayek, pro parte). Rosettes rather squarrose. Leaves 5-20 × 1-3 mm, linear to narrowly oblong, acute or apiculate. Flowering stem 6-20 cm, with 8-20 flowers. Inflorescence dark purplish-crimson. 2n = 12.{\i  Limestone rocks, usually above }1800{\i  m. Balkan peninsula, from Crna Gora and C. Bulgaria southwards}. Al Bu Gr Ju.
